 and practices have served to shape our limited response to the problem. Equally important, they consider how a more just, human-rights-based approach might be effected.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHomeless personsxServices forzUnited States. 0aHomeless persons-Services for-United States. 0aHomelessnessxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aHomelessnesszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aHomelessness-Government policy-United States. 0aHomelessness-United States-History. 0aUnited States-Social policy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Poverty & Homelessness.2bisacsh1 aTwiss, Pamela C., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311078354440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978162637797440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781626377974423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781626377974/original  a978-3-11-078354-4  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK